a: Personal colour is lilac. Also showjumps. Bogey fence is Huntsman's Close. Married Gary Stevens after he proposed at the press conference after Gemma's first 5* win in 2021 on Chilli Knight.
Terrifyingly good dressage.

Originally AUS, naturalised in 2006 after residing in the USA for 15 years. Has very cute horse bios on his website. Reduced his string since 2016 when his stepdaughter suffered a serious TBI in a horse fall.
Known for stylish appearance and high speed across country. Polishes his boots when nervous.
Day job as a dentist. Was encouraged by seeing fellow dentist Henrich Romeike at Badminton 2007. Won the CCI2* at Blair in 2016 while still a dentistry student (qualified in 2018).
Used to be a dairy farmer. Teammate Andrew Nicholson says he could go cross-country on a cow. Wanted to be a jockey but he's 6'2".
Based in Cheshire. Dodgy shoulder, had it operated in autumn 2024. His federation prioritises the Olympics over the 5*s.

Full name is William Speed Lane Fox-Pitt. Went to Eton, and the 'Pitt' is the same line as the former PM. Usually the tallest in the field at 6'5". Also breeds chickens. Suffered head trauma falling from Reinstated at Le Lion d'Angers October 2015, two weeks in ICU.
First job was as an apprentice bank clerk.
Married to a Grand Prix dressage rider. Co-hosts on the Eventing Radio Show. Lost six horses in a barn fire in 2011, then came 7th at Burghley with a horse that had suffered smoke inhalation.
Based in Wiltshire with husband Tim. Non-horsey background, dad was a butcher. Dropped out of a law undergraduate to event.
Given name means 'Blackbird'. Has a master's degree in Dutch & fiscal law.
Suspended for nine months in 2019 for breaking his whip over a pony at a XC clinic. He didn't even get it over the jump.
Runs the Billy stud with husband William. First winner of the Rolex Grand Slam in 2003. Writes children's books.
No relation. Mother Jane also went to Badminton and Burghley. Married to Ben King, who rides National Hunt. First rider to represent Team GB at Pony, Junior, Young Rider and Senior Europeans.
Entitled to ride in Italian police uniform. Moved to France in 2010 as it has better competing. Father was a high jumper (not puissance - track and field).
Was a part-time maths teacher for a bit. Parents were in showing and hunting.
Thoroughbred fan. Married to a cattle farmer. Rode Western as a child. Had a rotational fall with Exultation in May 2015, broken ribs and liver surgery, three days in ICU.
Younger brother of Felix.
Badminton debut in 2025. Based locally near Tetbury. Went to the Olympics in 2016.
The calmest man in eventing. Beach bum who doesn't like wearing shoes.
Personal colour: orange. The daughter of a 'non-horsey' dirt bike racer, got riding lessons for her sixth birthday. Trained by Karen and David O'Connor.

Three Olympics, the first Swiss 5* win in recent memory at Luhmuhlen in 2022, the World Cup in 2012, and multiple appearances at European Championships. Has a Golden Riding Badge, trained at Warendorf with Michi. Also showjumps internationally.
PhD in Irish insolvency law. Moved from showjumping to eventing when he met his wife, who came to see a horse he was selling. She bought it. They run MGH Sport Horses together.
Used to event her dad's failed racehorses in Australia. Relocated to the UK in 2005. Supergroom is Helen Tagg, known as 'Hels'. Survived breast cancer in 2018.
Was just showjumping til 2015. The national federation asked him to consider eventing because they needed another rider.

Born in Cumbria of Scottish heritage, now based in Perth. Enjoys golf and pickleball. Dad James completed Badminton, but it's his mum and stepdad who come to his shows. Aunt is Frances Hay-Smith, though I don't know on which side.
Nickname bestowed by an older sister, after Piglet from Winnie the Pooh. Used to date Oliver Townend.
Proud amateur with a 'normal job'. Took two horses to college, then cut down to just Fric Frac Berence to focus on work.
Dad and brother are equine vets, mother hunted. Did work experience with Nicola Wilson, then worked for Oliver Townend for a bit. Based in Yorkshire.
Based in Yorkshire. Hunts with the Bedale.
Brought up on a dairy farm in Kihikihi. First job was grooming for Mark Todd. His middle name is Clifton. Broke his neck falling from Cillnabradden Evo at Gatcombe August 2015.
Blogged at Horse & Hound for a couple of years. Same birthday as Mark Todd (1st March). Has done TV presenting. Owns a whippet. Three months off in 2013 with DVT.
Best remembered with the grey Lenamore, they went to the Olympics in 2008 and 2012. Briefly worked as a jockey as a young woman.
Personal colour is baby pink. Based in Wiltshire. Won the Nations Cup in 2017 with Halltown Harley. Changed nationality in 2022 after marrying an Irish rider, Toby Goss.
Amateur eventer and full-time equine vet.

Colour is black, for New Zealand. Worked as a rider for Andrew Nicholson. Taller than William Fox-Pitt at 6'6". Non-horsey family - dad is a doctor, mum teaches art. Wife was Georgie Strang who died at Bicton in 2024.
Also schools racehorses. Team gold at Tokyo with London 52. Had a rotational fall with Tis A Beauty at Tweseldown July 2013, collapsed lung, six days in ICU.
Based near Cirencester. Eventing geek - says he can list every Badminton winner. First 5* was in 2018 with Possible Mission.
Born in Lancashire. Dad raced motor cars. Sells sport horses under the Shadow prefix. Was 'the cob guy' until Mulrys Error retired in 2018. Big deal on the Insta. #yehBoi Survived cancer in 2015.
From the Alps, now based in Shropshire.
Dad Bobby is an event vet. Based at Gatcombe.
Used to be in a pop group called Paperdolls, toured with Boyzone.
Born in Grenoble. In another life, would have liked to be a rock singer.

Dad inherited Grandma's horse-drawn milk float, and ended up riding at Burghley as an amateur. Oliver is the first pro in the family. Old-fashioned and more than a bit chippy, rails about frangible pin penalties and doesn't have horse bios on his website. Used to date Piggy French (March).
Also trained as an equine dentist. Was reserve for the 2008 and 2012 Olympics. Sister Bryony also competes. Listed 'sleeping' on his interests when asked.
Biggest compliment to a horse is 'blood'. Prefers willingness in a horse to raw talent. Likes chocolate too much, cuts down before big events.
Broke his pelvis falling from Sarah d'Argouges at Bramham 2017.
Personal colour is sky blue.
Burghley first-time blogger for H&H in 2019. Gave up the day job as a quantity surveyor to start her eventing yard after her mother died in 2014. Her father James evented. Also snowboards.
Father is Con Power, a national showjumper.
Personal colour is bright red; aka the Red Thunder from Down Under.
Lost left ring finger to a freak accident in his horsebox at Bramham 2017. Has modified his rein grip to cope. Also had a foot crushed in a different freak accident in 2016.
Has been world number 1, and has won three 5* in one season. Only 5'2" and could never run fast enough to trot up Allstar B. 'Naturally a slowcoach', gets time faults if she's not careful.
Penalised for going too fast at her first pony cross-country.
Based in Tyne and Wear. Only started riding in 2011, when he was 13. Great-nephew of Badminton veteran Eric Thompson. Rides a motorbike and wants to do an Ironman race.

Wears brightly coloured trousers at trot-ups. Son of Richard Meade, was apprenticed to William Fox-Pitt. Proposed to his girlfriend during a Badminton course walk. 'Probably the nicest man in BE.' Shattered both elbows in a rotational at Wellington August 2013, then fell and was dragged in late 2020. Always comes back!
Runs a yard near Keysoe. Dreams of going to the Olympics.
A reserve firefighter. Yard burned down in 2018 - he was at Luhmuhlen at the time, and WhatsApp'd his firefighter mates to get there quick.
Trained under Bruce Davidson Sr. Admired his horse Eagle Lion and had signed posters of him.
Took a lot of 2018 off with a lingering concussion. Badminton first-timer blogger for H&H in 2015.
No, not that one. Plays golf.
Farrier and ex semi-pro rugby player. Introduced to eventing by his wife. Three daughters who all ride. He's a farrier, you know (he's not a farrier any more)
Born in Australia. Runs a livery yard in Wiltshire. Went to the Olympics in 2004 with Silence.
Likes hiking, fishing, kayaking, outdoor swimming.
Played for England in U16 hockey. Runs half-marathons for fun.
Actually wants to be a PE teacher.
Likes snowboarding and mountain biking.
Trying to develop a new equine hydrotherapy system. Broke his leg falling from Tarastro at Jardy July 2018.

Trained by Pippa Funnell. Dad is a farrier and does his horse's shoes. Trying to cut down on superstition, but throws new purchases on the floor so they've fallen once. Literal party trick: can juggle. Broke his leg falling from Newmarket Prospect at Hartpury August 2019.
Family is sporting but not horsey - has siblings in hockey and athletics. Got a pony when she was 10.
Won a round-trip flight to Europe in the 2017 US national 3* championship and used it to take OBOS O'Reilly to Badminton 2018. Trained by Karen and David O'Connor.
Tiny waifish rider on big horses. Broke her pelvis in a schooling accident in December 2015, after breaking her shoulder in October.
Dad trained racehorses, mother was a Team GB showjumper. Tina helps her brother on his race yard in Sussex. Broken shoulder in 2018.
Irish, based in Bedfordshire. Worked with the Wiegersmas when he was 19. Supports Everton.
Was pure dressage until she was 18. Also a qualified dive master. Goes mountain biking with her adult son.
Represents the Italian police force and is entitled to ride and trot-up in uniform. Also does mixed martial arts.
Husband Ben also events, as an amateur. From a racing family.
Has run three Tough Mudders.
Crowdfunded her trip to Badminton 2017.
Breeds exotic birds in his spare time.
Daughter of the Princess Royal, and godmother to Prince George. Married to a rugby player.
First ever Belgian 5* winner, after going double clear at Luhmuhlen. Married to Kai-Steffen Meier.

Runs the Opposition stud near Salisbury, founded with the Trakehner stallion Fleetwater Opposition by father John Johnston. Mum Debbie rode GP dressage. Married to fellow competitor Arthur Chabert (FRA).
Born in Florida. Superstitious: lucky red socks, and changes his breeches for each ride. Personal colour: red and white.

Based in the UK since 1994. Also works for the Monart Sales. Writes a blog at BillLevett.com, with loads of photos of the horses and reports on events. Good singing voice, has done panto. Used to drive cattle in Australia.
Daughter of Mary King. Personal colour is lavender. Based in Cheshire with her boyfriend. Ran the London Marathon in 2024.
Based out of Somerford Park. Brand is AH Eventing. Has done the Olympics.
Tina Cook's cousin. Is also a senior master of hounds.
Won best dressed at Badminton 2019 with an outfit fitting her Scottish heritage. Sister Beanie is a professional skier.
Based at the Ballybolger stud and will only ride Irish blood. Married to Hannah AKA Sparkles. Founded EquiRatings in 2014 with Diarm Byrne. Co-hosts on the EquiRatings Eventing Podcast.
Was exercising racehorses at 11, grew up on a racing yard. Dad rode National Hunt. Got suspended in 2013 after a fistfight at a party.
Events the King's horses - Marley isn't one of them. Completed Burghley in 2013, would have been back sooner but she had an injury (then a pandemic, then a baby).
Married to Padraig McCarthy.
Has a degree in microbiology from Reading. Dad Mark has been team vet to Olympic equestrians.
Double major in Literature and Foreign Affairs, Middle East expert. Trained by Boyd Martin.
Mum ran a hireling yard, Emma trained them to jump. Worked in sales until 2009, does after-dinner speaking on personal development. Also showjumps.
Based in Wiltshire. Full-time job in medical device sales, but did grow up hunting. Schools on grass and says this improves calmness in dressage.

Has three brothers who all also ride. Close ties to William Fox-Pitt, Hector's father owned one of William's Burghley winners and Hector rode some of William's horses after the 2015 fall. Broke a femur in a fall in early 2021.
Remarkable Badminton card photo of her trotting-up in a dirndl. Also scuba dives.
Has a business degree and worked as brand manager for a novelty umbrella company. Burghley first-timer blogger for H&H in 2018.
Trains the Thai national team. Caught a suspension over there once because his catch ride had been doped. White with a strong jaw and mousy hair - Eventing Nation thinks he's very handsome.
Also races cars and presents on TV. Broke her neck falling from HHS Cooley at Burgham July 2016, horse broke a leg and had to be euthanised.
Day job as a vet. Also breeds and trains dogs.
Chartered surveyor, runs her own business.

5* debut at Burghley 2023. Taller than his horse, who is 'normal sized' according to Tilly Berendt - genuinely can't find a height for the animal. Has two metal plates in his right hip after a 2013 fall.
Badminton debut in 2025. Comes from a horsey family near Stuttgart. Nations Cup team in 2022.
Won best dressed at Pau in 2018.
Broke his entire face at Ocala January 2009, repaired with 3 metal plates and 25 screws.
Loves cleaning tack. Didn't ride til he was 13. Hobbies are cross-country running, downhill mountain biking, and taking cars to bits. Badminton first-timer blogger for H&H in 2019.

Badminton debut in 2025, as reigning World Champion (with Banzai Du Loir). Won British championships at U16, U18 and U21. Grew up on the Isle of Man, now based in Cheshire. Was reserve for the Olympics in 2024.
Not from a horsey family, started lessons at four and got her first horse at 18 (produced by Louise Skelton). Also showjumps to a high level.
Tom Crisp calls her 'Flat White'. She likes coffee.

Accounts manager for a telecoms company. Got the news she was going to the CIC2* Europeans while in a meeting. Based in Kent, commutes to London. Since having a kid, has reduced her horses to a couple of broodmares and her 5* Dizzy.
Due to an old slipped disc causing femoral nerve damage, uses a modified saddle. Walks courses with the help of an electric bike.
Former science teacher.
Not the Canadian YouTuber. Grew up on a dairy farm; his yard is now based there. Mum Maggie also evented. Sells dad's ice-cream as a side hustle.

Personal colour: red. AKA Smokey Joe, after Smokey Joe Myers. Family owns the stud that bred Charisma (Mark Todd) and Silence (Dan Jocelyn). Now based in Florida. Also snowboards. Website is a Web 1.0 clunker and he doesn't keep it up to date.
Strong feelings on treating horses right - they get three months off in the field in the off season. Married to a racehorse trainer.
Based in a tiny village three hours from Sydney. First rider to win Adelaide three times, with Willinga Park Clifford. Showjumped and rode cowhorses before getting into eventing in 2010.
Born in Australia but doesn't like to talk about it - identifies strongly as Kiwi, though now based in GB. Spent two years living on a boat on the Pacific as a kid. Badminton debut in 2025.

BSc in agriculture science, works as a business analyst at a dairy farming business with 8000 cows. Currently on sabbatical and based near Cheltenham. Mother is Olympic eventer Tinks Pottinger n√©e White, grandmother is national dressage champion Tiny White n√©e Groome.
Misspelled 'Philpot' sometimes. Sold up and relocated to the UK for a few years to see how it goes. Based at Ruy Fonseca's yard.
Based in California. Daughter Kaylawna Smith-Cook also competes.
Trained by Buck Davidson. Collects shoes. Very tall, six foot. Not related to Boyd.
Only 5'1" and looks daft on 17.2hh Polaris. Kickboxes for a hobby. Religious, prays and meditates before competing.

Personal colour: baby blue. Non-horsey family. Introduced to horses aged eight at Girl Scout camp. Favours OTTBs. Was once sued by Stormy Daniels - rumours of poor horse care, unpaid debts, over-horsed Pony Club kids, and loose dogs at events.
Wanted to be a gymnast til she broke her ankle. 'Grew up in a divorced family' and worked at McDonalds from age 15. Likes American football, supports Philadelphia. Trained by Buck Davidson.

Grew up on a cattle ranch in west Texas, now based in North Carolina. Was a student under Philip Dutton. TBI and months of rehab in 1999, lightning burned his house down in 2004, broke his neck falling from Hans Dampf at Five Points in 2015. Got a skull and crossbones tattoo for his comeback. Likes Captain Hook.
16 years as a stockbroker before she went pro.
Also rides Grand Prix jumpers. Known for his height, he's 6'3" and most of his horses are also tall.
Knew she wanted to event at 13 when she saw a poster of Karen O'Connor jumping into a water complex. Now trains with Karen! Parents aren't horsey, both are psychologists.
Californian based outside of Swindon. Also competed in Irish dancing.
Wears socks with owls on, in order to make wise decisions across country.
Husband Scott is an equine vet. Brother Greig is a farrier for Team GB. Enjoys producing young horses.
Badminton debut in 2025. Identifies as a farmer who events, not as an eventer, but his dad did go to the Olympics as did he in 2024.
Got suspended in 2013 after a fistfight at a party, then fined in 2018 for faking vaccination records.
Used to ride a spotted eventer named Colby II. Based in Devon, also coaches.
Career ended by a fall from Veronica at Morven Park October 2012, landed on her head with multiple broken vertebrae.
Took some time off to have daughter Florence in 2021.

Based in Denmark. Also fly-fishes. Married to a dressage rider. Seems to have bad luck with fence judges. Wore a pin badge to support Ukraine, as Lithuania is a near neighbour, also has an XC hat silk knitted by his nana.
Lost some of his rides in 2015 while recovering from a car accident. Did his first Badminton with Stormstay in 2009.
Based near Lion d'Angers.
Not seen at Badminton since 2007 (Miss Ferrari). Is a dentist in real life.
Based in East Sussex. Mum Vicky also rode at Badminton. Uses the South Downs as her gallops.
From Country Down, grew up on a National Hunt yard. Now based near Kettering. Trained with Piggy French. Went to the Olympics 2024 with Wellfields Lincoln. Max Warburton's girlfriend.
Married to Kirsty n√©e Johnston of the Opposition stud. Won a Best Dressed at Burghley in 2019.
Runs a yard near Marlborough. Non-horsey family but dad was an Olympic cross-country skier. Does Crossfit, as if eventing wasn't dangerous enough.
Has dual nationality, now riding for the USA. Dad Nigel runs Aston-le-Walls and mum competed for the US.
Burghley debut in 2023. Based in Lincolnshire on his parents' farm. Loves Formula 1, will be trying to watch the racing between rides.
Badminton debut in 2025 aged 40. Set up Dassett Eventing in 2008, there are many Dassett ISH on this list. Based in Warwickshire.
Comes from Fife. Skipped university to work at a yard.

Burghley first-timer in 2022 - nearly qualified in 2016 but had a horse injury. Non-horsey parents, though Dad's in agricultural machinery. Came up through Pony Club. Born in Yorkshire, and lives in Stamford now! Seems like a really nice boy.

Keeps getting misprinted as 'Kyle'. Definitely a girl. Also teaches - yard website is authentically hideous. Hero-worshipped Nick Skelton. 'Not academic' - likes to make things. Breeding prefix is Kinda.
Parents not horsey, was self-taught as a child on borrowed ponies. Worked weekends for the Pox-Pitts and saved up for one of his own. Now lives very near Burghley.
Manages a livery in Surrey.
Non-horsey parents, took riding lessons in Toronto. Now based near Cirencester. Married a British eventer named Emma, who had lived in the US for a bit.

Based in Pennsylvania, and Florida in the winter. Rode for Chris Burton before relocating to the USA. Owns a dog called Vegemite and married to a Texan woman called Jimmie. Badminton card lists 'video games' as his hobby. Made some training videos as 'Evention TV'. Blogged about his first-time Badminton for Chronicle of the Horse in 2022.
Studied business in Delaware, and now runs Flynn Sport Horses, importing, training and selling on. Trained under Phillip Dutton.
Based in North Carolina. Grew up on a farm in New Hampshire.
Good hair. Good face, honestly. Once took Unmarked Bills down the jog strip in a leather jacket and leather trousers.
Badminton debut in 2025. Based in County Durham. Non-horsey background and non-horsey husband (although she's converted him now).
Burghley first-timer blogger in 2019. Likes to play darts. Broke a rein at Le Pin au Haras 2019 and had to canter in circles til Efraim agreed to stop.
Works at the Billy stud. Mother and sister also event. Website is full of template text and JPEG artifacts.
Studied Agriculture. Holds the German Golden Riding Badge. The Wahler line runs a Trakehner stud.
A pupil of Michi Jung. Lives in Germany, competes for Sweden through heritage.

Based near Swindon. Riding school kid, been BE since she was 12. Trains with Carl Hester and likes watching dressage - not mad keen on showjumping, and very tempted by dark horses with white feet. Lost her stabling in 2020 and lived in her lorry for a couple of months. Owns three chihuahuas.

First competitor at Badminton born after the millennium, I think. Idolised Oliver Townend and William Fox-Pitt. Mother is eventer Caroline Casburn n√©e Sizer, Alice tends to ride Caroline's homebreds.
Based in Yorkshire. Also hunts.
Based out of France.
From Ontario, based in Florida. Family moved to the country when he was 7, he hadn't ridden before that.
Has a 2.1 in law. Blogged for H&H for a number of years.

During university, was flying back and forth between Newmarket and Edinburgh. Her dissertation in sports management was due the week before Badminton 2022. Broke her back in 2021 and then again in 2023, isn't modern medicine wonderful? 'Half of my spine [is] made of metal.' Was British under-25 national champion and has an absolutely iron will.
Parents were British. Took French nationality, based in France.
Degree in biology, masters in teaching.
Son of an Olympic eventer, but didn't ride til he was 14.

From Wisconsin, based in Pennsylvania. Pupil of Phillip Dutton. Training for her yoga teacher certificate. The sort of person who has a 'motivational quote of the day' calendar, and then blogs about it.

Amateur - has a masters in investment banking, a day job at KPMG, and no groom! Originally rode GBR, switched to NZL in 2022 (her dad is Kiwi). Hero-worshipped Pippa Funnell and Mary King as a kid. Birthday is 1st September, so overlapped Burghley in 2023.
Badminton debut in 2025.
Grew up on a farm in Brazil. Met Mark Todd when he was coaching the national team, trained under him in Wiltshire then under William Fox-Pitt.
Trains with Andrew Nicholson and the Prices.
Badminton debut in 2025. Yard is in Berkshire. Also boxes.
Based in Wiltshire. Dreamed of Badminton and Burghley - has an aunt in England.
5* debut at Burghley 2023. Based in Yorkshire. Won Best Dressed at Bramham once.
Badminton debut in 2023. Parents met at a British Juniors team training camp, whole family is industry - Georgia was on ponies before she could walk, and won a lot on them.
Based in West Yorkshire. Ridden since she was 18 months, evented since she was 14. Idolises Pippa Funnell - felt lucky to have the same birthday.
Learned from Andrew Nicholson and Sam Griffiths, these days has his own yard in Surrey. Grew up in Mayenne, so he's Mayennais. Also showjumps.
5* debut at Burghley 2023. Turned pro in 2021.
Born in Australia, moved to the UK aged 8 and learned to ride. Has a twin brother Silas who's an equine vet. Was in pony club at Burghley.

Badminton debut in 2025. Based outside Brussels. Dad Kris still competes, as does Senne's sister. Tragically, is a tech bro, whose LinkedIn is on the first page of his Google results. Mainly works in test automation.
5* debut in 2024. Based in County Wexford. Also plays squash.
5* debut in 2024 on Monbeg Exclusive. Goes to the World Young Horse Championships. Susie Berry's boyfriend.
5* debut Burghley 2023, Badminton debut in 2025 as the youngest rider in the field. Coached by mum Fran. Plays hockey.

f: Vina BULLER (IRL) Not found in database

a: Burghley first-timer in 2023. Blames herself for Bally Louis's showjumping issues. Another fan of leather leggings at trot-ups.
Son of Philippe Marx. Runs his own yard near Paris. Part-time job in a stationery shop, but would like to quit!
Badminton debut in 2025, holding 'most accented characters in name'. Dad also competed. Based out of the German state riding school at Warendorf. Trots up in uniform as a 'sports soldier' (?).
Badminton debut in 2025. Comes from a family that produces showjumpers and eventers, and he helps ride the youngsters, but Arne has a Masters and works full time for the council.
Badminton debut in 2025. An amateur with a Masters in supply chain engineering and a full-time job. Plays padel. Dad and granddad both competed. Trains with Kai-Steffan Meier, based in Belgium.
Local to Burghley. Mother and sister are also equestrians. Showjumped on ponies as a kid. First moved up to advanced with Quarry Man.
Badminton debut in 2025. Was captain of the equestrian club at uni. Ireland's leading rider in 2020. Always goes to the world young horse championships.

Yard is near Cirencester. Non-horsey background, got lessons starting when she was eight. Parents sold their car to buy her a Cooley when she was 17. Went to the European Cup in 2019 with Geluk G. Has a dog named Dora.
Badminton debut in 2025.

Badminton debut in 2025. Amateur based in Belgium, works for a road-building company. Wouter's uncle Dirk was the first Belgian to compelte Badminton, and Wouter dreamed of following him. Was European champion on ponies in 2002.
5* debut at Badminton 2025. Gloucestershire-based, supports Man United, and couldn't think of anything interesting to say on his bio - 'likes socialising with friends'? Well, he is only 23.
Badminton debut in 2025. Non-horsey family, but partner hunts (queer???) Runs Jack Mantel Sport Horses.
Badminton debut in 2025. Based in Dorset. Also rides and teaches dressage.
5* debut in 2024. Based in County Meath. Also plays Gaelic football.
